<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet href="\\Ameras0036\Data\BIEM_PRODUCTION_AMERICA\053_NJT\Application\p-xml\XSL\053_NJT_ib.xslt" type="text/xsl"?><!--thru 053_NJT_p-iem_IB.xslt--><ib miid="BOM01298" doc-type="MI" maint-item-desc="Communication Control Panel" part-number="05384180061S" doc-name="BOM01298_MI" doc-title="Communication Control Panel" lock-counter="10" search-index="mim-sys9-dno" show-e-list="yes" e-list-number="09 01 02" giid-maint-item-desc="Communication Control Panel" id-document="25916" id-document-version="40165" doc-version="0" pmt-version="14" gmt-version="12" user-defined-1="" user-defined-2="" user-defined-3="" oem-part-no="" device-name="CCP"><maintenance-item><para reuse="all">The Communication Control Panel (CCP) allows
crew members to access the train audio communication system. </para><para reuse="all">CCP units are located throughout the cars (see
Figure <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDIIFEH"></iref></ref-container> and
Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDBDJGG"></iref></ref-container>),
mounted in recessed openings in the partition wall liners. The unit
weighs approximately 11 lb and measures approximately 10.8 in.
high, 8.0 in. wide, and 4.0 in. deep. The panel
face is brushed stainless steel and the body is aluminum with a
chemical conversion coating. </para><illustration reuse="all"><graphic file="..\..\Graphics\CGM\053J-751-011.cgm" cropped="1" float="0" height="5.70in" impsize="9.00in 5.70in"></graphic><title id="CHDIIFEH">Communication Control Panel</title></illustration><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="CHDBDJGG">CCP Location</title><tgroup cols="5" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="3.000in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" valign="middle">UNIT ID</entry><entry colname="2" morerows="1" valign="middle">LOCATION</entry><entry namest="3" nameend="5">QTY/CAR</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="3">C</entry><entry colname="4">S</entry><entry colname="5">T</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" align="center">CCP1</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">F-end, Cab Rear Wall</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">-</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="left">A-end, End Vestibule</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">CCP2</entry><entry colname="2">B-end, End Vestibule</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="center">CCP3</entry><entry colname="2">Toilet Outside Wall</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">-</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">The panel face is engraved with label text permanently
marked in black, and pierced to provide protection grills for a
speaker and for an array of three microphones. Various indicators
and controls are also found on the panel face (see Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDJHFBJ"></iref></ref-container>). The rotary switch
is operated with the NJ Transit standard coach key.</para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="CHDJHFBJ">CCP Controls and Indicators</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.750in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">LABEL</entry><entry colname="2">TYPE</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">PUSH TO TALK</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Pushbutton</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Activates CCP transmissions.</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">PEI ACTIVATED</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">LED Indicator</entry><entry colname="3" align="left"></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">OFF</entry><entry colname="2" morerows="3">Rotary Switch/Selector</entry><entry colname="3" morerows="3">Activates the corresponding
communication mode. Operated using the NJ Transit standard coach
key.</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">PA</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">IC</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1">PEI</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">Two car wiring cables are connected to the CCP
through an 8-pin plug (at connector <verbatim>J1</verbatim>) and
a 12-pin plug (at connector <verbatim>J2</verbatim>). (See Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDJHECD"></iref></ref-container>.) A ground wire connects
the CCP to the carbody. </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="CHDJHECD">CCP Connections</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.750in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">PLUG ID</entry><entry colname="2">PIN NO.</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">GND</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="3">Carbody ground</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" align="center">P1</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1,2</entry><entry colname="3">Power (supplied by CCU)</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">4,5</entry><entry colname="3">Panel location and identification jumper pins</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">P2A</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1,2,3,4</entry><entry colname="3">RS-485 Audio Control Network (shared by the
CCCP and all CCPs and PEIs)</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="center">P2B</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">5,6</entry><entry colname="3">Dedicated CCP audio channel (from CCU, one
channel for each CCP)</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></maintenance-item></ib>